Vibes LaunchPoint Service Error: Vibes Login Credentials Invalid

The Vibes LaunchPoint Service needs accurate and up-to-date username, password, and Company API Key credentials to establish a connection with an account within Vibes. The Company API Key is provided by Vibes and does not change. However, the username and password can be changed by the account holder within Vibes; causing a disruption to the LaunchPoint Service in Marketo.

It is possible the account holder changed their username and/or password while logged into their Vibes account. Please check with the account holder and update the Vibes LaunchPoint Service in Marketo with the new credentials.

Push Notification Send Error: Google/Android Credentials Invalid For %appName%
Marketo can no longer send push notifications to an app when the Google API credentials have been removed or the Google Cloud API for your app has been disabled.

Google uses credentials (Project Number and API Key) for each app registered by a developer. When the API key has been removed or the Google Cloud API for your app has been disabled, Marketo can no longer send push notifications to the app on your behalf.

Go to the Google Cloud Platform console and ensure that the API key exists and the Google Cloud API for your app is enabled. Then update the credentials in Marketo Admin > Mobile Apps & Devices > Push Access. Then run Mobile App Actions > Verify Push Configuration to confirm the credentials are working.
Push Notification Send Error: Apple/iOS Certificate Revoked For %appName%
Marketo can no longer send push notifications to an app when the Apple-supplied iOS certificate for that app has been revoked.

Apple issues a unique iOS certificate for each app registered by a developer. When a certificate is revoked by Apple, Marketo can no longer send push notifications to the associated app on your behalf.

Please obtain a valid certificate for your app from Apple. You will need to upload the new certificate in Marketo Admin > Mobile Apps & Devices > Push Access. Then you'll need to run Mobile App Actions > Verify Push Configuration to confirm the new certificate is working.
Marketo can no longer send push notifications to an app when the Apple-supplied certificate for that app has expired.

Apple issues a unique certificate - along with an expiration date - for each app registered by a developer. When a certificate expires, Marketo can no longer send push notifications to the associated app on your behalf.

Please obtain a new certificate from Apple for your app. You will need to upload the new certificate for this app in Marketo Admin > Mobile Apps & Devices. Then you'll need to run Mobile App Actions > Verify Push Configuration to confirm the new certificate is working.
